  "market_context": "Uptrend on EUR/USD 4H chart with impulsive moves upward followed by pullbacks. Price repeatedly retraced to prior resistance levels that had flipped to support, offering repeated long entries.",
  "key_observation": "The analyst highlighted how a prior resistance level at ~0.9220–0.9245 repeatedly acted as support during pullbacks in an ongoing uptrend, creating multiple high-probability buying zones.",
  "analysis_steps": [
    "Step 1: Identify the impulsive move upward and subsequent pullback on the 4H USDEUR chart.",
    "Step 2: Draw the prior resistance level (e.g., around 0.9220–0.9245) that was broken during the impulsive move.",
    "Step 3: Observe that price pulled back to that broken resistance level, which now functioned as support, presenting a buying opportunity.",
    "Step 4: Note that this pattern repeated across multiple pullbacks—price consistently returned to the same flipped resistance zone.",
    "Step 5: Acknowledge a failed case where price briefly broke below the flipped level but the uptrend remained intact as long as the prior swing low held."
  ],
  "outcome": null,
  "lessons": "Resistance flipping to support is a reliable price action signal in trending markets; however, confirmation (e.g., candlestick patterns, structure hold) is essential to avoid false breakouts and losing trades.",
